      "writtenOn": "2018-08-30T14:59:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually my recommendation would be to redesign SnapshotPipe so that signaling snapshot operations in read/write is separate from doing them:\n\nWe should not stop the VM or do any operation in the middle of a read/write call, where the contract really seems to be to not interfere with pipe device pointers which might get invalidated on snapshot operations.\n\nInstead, there should be a different object or thread that handles the snapshot operation, performs it, and then the read/write protocol in the guest should be changed so that it does not happen in one \"read/write\" command; write once to do a snapshot operation, and then in a separate call to the pipe, read it back.\n\nOn the host, the write will dispatch the snapshot operation, and the snapshot operation will do all the save/load/remapping. After that, the snapshot operation object will signal the SnapshotPipe to signal the guest.\n\nThe guest should be able to safely spin or poll() the qemu pipe driver for data available for reading, like in goldfish-opengl:\n\nwhile (res \u003e 0) {\n        ssize_t stat \u003d ::read(m_sock, (char *)(buf) + len - res, res);\n        if (stat \u003d\u003d 0) {\n            // client shutdown;\n            return NULL;\n        } else if (stat \u003c 0) {\n            if (errno \u003d\u003d EINTR) {\n                continue;\n            } else {\n                ERR(\"QemuPipeStream::readFully failed (buf %p, len %zu\"\n                    \", res %zu): %s, lethal error, exiting.\", buf, len, res,\n                    strerror(errno));\n                abort();\n            }\n        } else {\n            res -\u003d stat;\n        }\n    }",
      "parentUuid": "4fece2b7_ec74f480",
